<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1124,1400]" box="[151,577,1124,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,577,1124,1149]" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" reason="2">
<taxonomicName authority="(Risso, 1816)" authorityName="Risso" authorityYear="1816" baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[151,577,1124,1149]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Acanthephyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelagica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,577,1124,1149]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,418,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">Acanthephyra pelagica</emphasis>
(Risso, 1816)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1124,1400]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">
Cosmopolitan, pelagic, recorded southern limit: 60°S, i.e. south of the Polar Front (
<bibRefCitation box="[1136,1300,1159,1184]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref29131" refString="Wasmer, R. A. (1986) Pelagic shrimps of the family Oplophoridae (Crustacea: Decapoda) from the Pacific sector of the Southern Ocean: USNS Eltanin Cruises 10, 11, 14 - 16, 19 - 21, 24, and 25. In: Biology of the Antarctic Seas XVII. Antarctic Research Series, 44, 29 - 68." type="journal article">Wasmer 1986</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref23232" refString="Iwasaki, N. &amp; Nemoto, T. (1987 a) Pelagic Shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) from the Southern Ocean between 150 ° E and 115 ° E. Memoirs of the National Institute of Polar Research, 38, 1 - 40." type="journal article">Iwasaki &amp; Nemoto 1987a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[339,500,1196,1220]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref29199" refString="Wasmer, R. A. (1993) Pelagic shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) from six USNS Eltanin cruises in the southeastern Indian Ocean, Tasman Sea, and southwestern Pacific Ocean to the Ross Sea. Antarctic Research Series, 58, 49 - 91." type="journal article">Wasmer 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[515,733,1196,1221]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref28467" refString="Tiefenbacher, L. (1994) Decapode Crustaceen aus westantarktischen Gewassern gesammelt von der R. V. &quot; John Biscoe &quot;, Reise 11. Spixiana, 17 (1), 13 - 19." type="journal article">Tiefenbacher 1994</bibRefCitation>
); also recorded between the Campbell and Antipode Islands (
<bibRefCitation box="[158,379,1231,1256]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref29248" refString="Webber, W. R., Fenaughty, C. M. &amp; Clark, M. R. (1990) A guide to some common offshore shrimp and prawn species of New Zealand. New Zealand Fisheries Occasional Publication, 6, 1 - 42." type="journal article">
Webber 
<emphasis box="[254,311,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">et al.</emphasis>
1990
</bibRefCitation>
), from Crozet Islands (
<bibRefCitation box="[638,798,1231,1256]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref24313" refString="Ledoyer, M. (1979) Caridea (Crustacea, Decapoda) des iles Kerguelen, Crozet, Marion et Prince Edward, et du sud de Madagascar (Banc Walters), des campagnes MD. 03, MD. 04 et MD. 08 du M / S &quot; Marion-Dufresne &quot;. In: Arnaud, P. M. &amp; Hureau, J. C. (Eds.), Campagne Oceanographique &quot; M. D. &quot; [&quot; Marion-Dufresne &quot;] 0 8 Benthos Aux Iles Crozet, Marion Et Prince Edward: Premiers Resultats Scientifiques. Comite National Francais des Recherches Antarctiques, Paris, 44, 137 - 153." type="journal article">Ledoyer 1979</bibRefCitation>
) and Argentinean Patagonia (
<bibRefCitation box="[1135,1281,1231,1256]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref28581" refString="Torti, M. R. &amp; Boschi, E. E. (1973) Nuevos aportes al conocimiento de los crustaceos decapodos Caridea del genero Campylonotus Bate, 1888. Physis, Seccion A, 32 (84), 65 - 84." type="journal article">Boschi 1973</bibRefCitation>
; Boschi 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">et al.</emphasis>
1981). Burukovsky &amp; Romensky (1982) restored the name 
<taxonomicName authority="Spence Bate, 1888" authorityName="Spence Bate" authorityYear="1888" box="[833,1133,1268,1292]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Acanthephyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sica">
<emphasis box="[833,911,1268,1292]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">A. sica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[920,1133,1268,1292]" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" refId="ref27094" refString="Spence Bate, C. S. (1888) Report on the Crustacea Macrura collected by H. M. S. Challenger during the Years 1873 - 76. In: Murray, J. (Ed.), Zoology. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger During the Years 1873 - 76, 24, pp. i - xc, 1 - 942, pls. 1 - 157." type="journal article">Spence Bate, 1888</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
for southern forms of this species, considered to have a more carinate carapace than the northern Atlantic form. This proposal has not gained wider acceptance and until the systematics of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Risso" baseAuthorityYear="1816" box="[705,833,1340,1365]" class="Malacostraca" family="Oplophoridae" genus="Acanthephyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="217" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pelagica">
<emphasis box="[705,833,1340,1365]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="217">A. pelagica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex are sorted, the Southern Ocean form is best retained under this name.
</paragraph>
